# 37Metrics — Personal defaults

This file **augments** [`37m-core.mdc`](37m-core.mdc). Together with the other `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files, it is the **source of truth for Cursor** in this workspace (no separate enterprise guidelines repo required).

## Repository naming

- kebab-case with `37m-` prefix: `37m-inventory-api`, `37m-shipping-portal`
- Always lowercase, hyphens only — no underscores or camelCase
- Add qualifier suffix when needed: `-api`, `-cli`, `-web`, `-mobile`, `-scripts`, `-infra`

## Technology stack (extended policy)

Follow these choices on all new projects unless the spec explicitly overrides:

| Type | Stack |
|------|-------|
| Web apps (internal) | Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui |
| Web apps (public) | Same + Auth0, Clerk, Supabase Auth, GitHub OAuth, AWS Cognito, or similar |
| Mobile | PWA-first; React Native only with a short written justification in the repo |
| Desktop | Tauri — only when a web app genuinely cannot meet the need |
| CLI tools | Python by default (typer/click, rich, Poetry) |
| APIs | Node.js (Express or Fastify) or Python (FastAPI) |
| NetSuite | SuiteScript 2.x only (when applicable) |
| Infrastructure | Terraform + GitHub Actions, or simpler hosting when enough |

**Prohibited on new projects:** Next.js, Angular, .NET, Yarn, pnpm, Bun

## Package management

- JavaScript/TypeScript: **npm only** — always commit `package-lock.json`
- Python: **Poetry** for non-trivial projects; pip + `requirements.txt` (pinned versions) for simple scripts — commit lock file
- Run `npm audit` regularly; fix critical/high issues promptly

## Authentication (choose based on context)

- Local tools / no multi-user server → **none** or API keys in env only
- Personal SaaS or side project → **Clerk**, **Supabase Auth**, **Auth0**, **GitHub OAuth**, or similar
- On-network Windows integration → **Active Directory** when relevant
- Microsoft 365 / Azure tenant → **Entra ID**
- AWS-hosted with external users → **AWS Cognito**

## Security

- Never commit secrets, `.env` files with real values, or credentials of any kind
- Commit `.env.example` with placeholder values and descriptions
- Secrets: env vars, `.env.local` (gitignored), OS keychain, 1Password CLI, GitHub Actions Secrets, or AWS Secrets Manager — pick what fits the project
- TLS 1.2+ required for all data in transit — no exceptions
- WCAG 2.1 Level AA for web and desktop UIs you ship to others
- Follow least-privilege access for all database and service credentials

## What must never be committed

- API keys, passwords, tokens, certificates with private keys
- `.env` files with real values (commit `.env.example` only)
- `node_modules/`, `.venv/`, `venv/`, `dist/`, `build/`, `.next/`
- `.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`, IDE files (`.idea/`)
- Database dumps or large binary files

## Required files in every application repository

- `README.md` — project overview, prerequisites, setup, env vars, scripts, deployment
- `.gitignore` — appropriate for the stack
- `.editorconfig` — standard formatting (see below)
- `.env.example` — all required env vars with placeholder values and descriptions

## EditorConfig (copy into application repos)

```ini
root = true

[*]
indent_style = space
indent_size = 2
end_of_line = lf
charset = utf-8
trim_trailing_whitespace = true
insert_final_newline = true

[*.md]
trim_trailing_whitespace = false

[*.py]
indent_size = 4
```

## Versioning

- Semantic versioning: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Store in `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, or `tauri.conf.json` as appropriate
- Tag releases in Git: `v1.2.0`
- Maintain `CHANGELOG.md` following Keep a Changelog format

## Accessibility

- WCAG 2.1 Level AA minimum for web UIs you publish
- shadcn/ui (Radix UI primitives) provides accessible defaults — never override accessibility attributes
- Sufficient color contrast, keyboard navigation, visible focus indicators, meaningful alt text
